com.github.rschmitt.collider

Class ClojureMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.rschmitt.collider.ClojureMap<K,V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Map<K,V>

    @Immutable
public class ClojureMap<K,V>
extends Object
implements Map<K,V>
    A generic persistent immutable Map implementation, with three types of methods:
    1. Read methods from Map, such as get(java.lang.Object)
    2. Write methods from Map, such as put(K, V); these will throw UnsupportedOperationException
      3. and have been marked as @Deprecated
    3. Persistent "modification" methods, such as assoc(K, V); these will efficiently create modified copies of the current map

      • assoc

        public ClojureMap<K,V> assoc(K key,
                             V value)
        Returns a copy of this map which also contains a mapping from key to value. If a mapping for key already exists in the current map, it will be overwritten.

      • dissoc

        public ClojureMap<K,V> dissoc(K key)
        Returns a copy of this map without a mapping for key.

      • merge

        @SafeVarargs
public final ClojureMap<K,V> merge(ClojureMap<K,V>... maps)
        Returns a map that consists of all bindings from the current map, as well as maps. If a mapping occurs in more than one map, the mapping in the rightmost map will take precedence.

      • toMutableMap

        public Map<K,V> toMutableMap()
